# ThreadSanitizer suppressions for known toolchain false positives.
#
# libstdc++'s timed mutexes acquire their locks through pthread_mutex_clocklock
# (and the shared variants through pthread_rwlock_clock*lock) when the platform
# provides them. Some libtsan builds - GCC's on current Ubuntu, for example -
# do not intercept those functions, so TSan never observes the lock and then
# misreports the perfectly matched unlock as "unlock of an unlocked mutex".
#
# These suppressions are scoped to the std timed mutex unlock frames only;
# genuine mutex misuse anywhere else still reports.
mutex:std::timed_mutex::unlock
mutex:std::recursive_timed_mutex::unlock
mutex:std::shared_timed_mutex::unlock
mutex:std::shared_timed_mutex::unlock_shared
